  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Enhancing community resilience and livelihoods recovery capacities.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">-Community mobilization and consultation meetings.
-Identification and registration of beneficiaries
-Procurement of project inputs (vegetable seeds, tools, fishing hooks and twines)
-Distribution of the inputs to project beneficiaries.
-Training of vegetable growing members on vegetable growing techniques
-Training fisher folk members on fish catching and preservation
-Post distribution monitoring
-Establishing 20 VSLA groups of 20 members. 
-Training of 20 VSLA groups on poverty reduction and social empowerment
-Provide VSLA kits (Saving boxes, collection baskets, sitting mats and passbooks).
-Post-harvest handling in vegetable production.
-Conduct conflict sensitive PVCA (Participatory Vulnerability Community Assessment)
-Implement community PVCA action plan</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improved food production and productivity through transfer of sustainable agricultural practices and technologies</narrative>
